@node Configuration
@chapter Configuration
@cindex configuration
@cindex application.ini

OwnSona reads every setting from a single file:
@file{src/main/backend/application.ini}.  The file is INI-format, all
keys live under the @code{[main]} section, and the servlet loads it
once at startup via Kiss's @code{MainServlet.readIniFile} mechanism.

The file is gitignored.  A template lives at
@file{src/main/backend/application.ini.example}; copy it on first
install and edit in place.

@b{When a change to @file{application.ini} takes effect.}  Editing the
source-tree copy alone does nothing.  The build (@code{./bld -v
build && ./bld war}) copies the file into the WAR.  When you replace
the deployed WAR, the servlet picks up the new values on next start.
Tomcat's @code{autoDeploy="true"} restarts the webapp automatically
about ten seconds after the WAR replaces the previous one; restart
the service explicitly with @code{systemctl restart ownsona.service}
if you want it immediate.

